===Verbs and verb phrases===

Mon verbs do not inflect for person. Tense is shown through particles.

Some verbs have a morphological causative, which is most frequently a /pə-/ prefix (Pan Hla 1989:29):

{| class=&quot;wikitable&quot;
|-
! Underived verb !! Gloss !! Causative verb !! Gloss
|-
| chɒt || to die || kəcɒt || to kill
|-
| lɜm || to be ruined || pəlɒm || to destroy
|-
| khaɨŋ || to be firm|| pəkhaɨŋ ||to make firm
|-
| tɛm || to know || pətɛm || to inform
|}

===Nouns and noun phrases===

====Singular and Plural====

Mon nouns do not inflect for number. That is, they do not have separate forms for singular and plural:

{|
|-
|
|{{my|၁}}
|
|-
| sɔt pakaw
| mo̤a
| me̤a
|-
| apple
| one
| classifier
|}
'one apple'

{|
|-
|
|{{my|၂}}
|
|-
| sɔt pakaw
| ba
| me̤a
|-
| apple
| two
| classifier
|}
'two apples'

====Adjectives====

Adjectives follow the noun (Pan Hla p.&amp;nbsp;24):

{|
|-
|prɛ̤a
|ce
|-
|woman
|beautiful
|}
'beautiful woman'

====Demonstratives====

Demonstratives follow the noun:

{|
|-
| ŋoa || nɔʔ
|-
| day || this
|-
|colspan=&quot;2&quot;|this day
|}

====Classifiers====

Like many other Southeast Asian languages, Mon has [[Classifier (linguistics)|classifiers]] which are used when a noun appears with a numeral. The choice of classifier depends on the semantics of the noun involved.

{| class=&quot;wikitable&quot; border=&quot;1&quot;
|-
!IPA
|kaneh
|mo̤a
|tanəng
|-
!Gloss
|pen
|one
|classifier
|}
'one pen'

{| class=&quot;wikitable&quot; border=&quot;1&quot;
|-
!IPA
|chup
|mo̤a
|tanɒm
|-
!Gloss
|tree
|one
|classifier
|}
'one tree'

===Prepositions and prepositional phrases===

Mon is a prepositional language.

{|
|-
|  doa||əma
|-
| in || lake
|-
|'in the lake'
|}

